<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="ruin-n">ruin <strong><em>n</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'ruːɪn/    美 /'ruːɪn/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1-u">1.★ <strong>[U] 毁灭；破产：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>the ruin of civilization 
文明的毁灭</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>financial ruin</strong> 
破产</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>fall in / into ruin</strong> 
灭亡；荒废</p></div>

<h4 id="2-c">2.★ <strong>[C] [常用复数] 废墟；遗迹；残余：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>the ruins of Rome 
古罗马遗迹</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="in-ruins">in ruins</h3>
<p>1.<strong>成废墟；严重受损：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>In fifteen terrible seconds a large city <strong>lay in ruins</strong>.
在可怕的15秒内，一座大城市就沦为一片废墟。</p><footer>人教① – 4</footer></div>

<h2 id="_3">派生词汇</h2>
<p>ruined /'ruːɪnd/ adj [只用于名词前]  </p></div>